title: [improvement](drop tablet) impr gc deleted tablet lock
body:
## Proposed changes

when gc a deleted tablet,  it need 1 rocksdb read +  2 rocksdb write + 1 directory move,  sometimes it will cost 20ms.
  
This thread will acquire the shutdown write lock and gc 200 tablets each run,  which up to 4s. So the shutdown lock will block 4s.   Then happen:  drop tablet thread  wait for shutdown lock for 4s,   also the drop tablet thread hold the tablet manager shard lock for 4s => create tablet thread will wait for shard thread for 4s.  => FE create partition need wait for long time.

Fix concurrency issue where some delta writer meets "close after closed" issue.
Because some sink may be closed before other sinks to be opened,
the reference count dropps to 0 and the pool will be closed when the load is not done.

To fix the problem, we should init delta writer pool in sink prepare.
Because there is a barrier between prepare and open.
All the sinks should have been prepared before any of them may close.

title: [Improvement](inverted index) delay inverted index col read to reduce IO
body:
## Proposed changes

Issue Number: close #xxx

Currently, match predicate eg.`msg MATCH 'error'` will be added to common expr `_common_expr_ctxs_push_down` to downgrade to text scan if  index is missing.  It causes a side effect that index column `msg` will be read at firstRead stage, which can be delayed to lazyRead stage to reduce IO. 

Noticeable performance degree is observed in the following query, if the selectivity of match predicate `msg MATCH 'error' ` is low but the selectivity of expr predicate `abs(c_bigint)` is high.
`SELECT * FROM test WHERE msg MATCH 'error' AND abs(c_bigint) < 100000`

This PR delete match predicate from common expr `_common_expr_ctxs_push_down` if the index is applied successfully.

title: [Enhancement](sql-cache) Use update time of hive to avoid cache miss through multi fe nodes.
body:
## Proposed changes

Now the update time of hms table is generated by every FE node (Use `System.currentTimestamp()` separately), so the update time of a hms table may be different between FE nodes, always the same query can not hit the sql-cache if we submit it more than one times through different FE nodes. This pr mainly do following changes to avoid this problem.

- Use the `transient_lastDdlTime` instead of `System.currentTimestamp` as the `schemaUpdateTime` of hms tables
- Use the `eventTime` in hms event instead of `System.currentTimestamp` as the update time when processing hms events

## Further comments

title: [improvement](tablet clone) furthur repair replicas should be check even if they are versions catchup
body:
## Proposed changes

pick: #25551

If there are loading txns, PR https://github.com/apache/doris/pull/24845 will try to furthur repair a balance tablet even if their versions are catchup.

Then in scheduler's NEED_FURTHER_REPAIR handler, if no replicas are version fallbehind, the sched ctx will convert to REPLICA_MISSING, then add missing replicas will fail because they don't really miss replicas.

Improvement: for NEED_FURTHER_REPAIR handler, if all the replicas are version catchup, then try to check the txns before further repair txn has finished, if it finished, then mark the replica as further repair finish.
